Bought this years ago because it was (1) one of the more useful alarms and (2) the maker didn't assume that everyone has 20/20 uncorrected vision at 4:35AM while struggling to turn of an alarm so it doesn't wake the whole house.  With the newest release, the maker seems to have joined the ranks of most other makers who seem to think everyone has perfect vision.   Used to be, to dismiss an alarm, there was a clear, distinctive, large white bar on my screen (that's all I could see, the text was too small). I just had to look for the white bar and tap it. That's gone.   Now there's a white square (again, with text way to small to be able to read) whose 95% area is dedicated to SNOOZE, NOT Dismiss. Somewhere in this square is some text, tiny, non-contrasting, that I can't find at 4:35AM. I accidentally tap the SNOOZE because there's a 95% chance that's what you're going to hit. The alarm keeps going off, waking my family.   I can make use of this during the day at the office, but I don't really need it due to Google Calendar. Still, it's not 1 star, so I will give it 2. Previously gave it 5. It's coming off my phone if the maker can't come to grips with reality.
